text: Onut (; ) is a commune (selsoviet) in Zastavna Raion, Chernivtsi Oblast, Ukraine. The village lies southwest of the Dniester. The Onut River runs through the village; one side is in the historic region of Bukovina, the other in Bessarabia. Category:Villages in Zastavna Raion
title: Onut, Zastavna Raion
